text: Kazhayevo () is a rural locality (a village) in Tungatarovsky Selsoviet, Uchalinsky District, Bashkortostan, Russia. The population was 57 as of 2010. There are 2 streets. == Geography == It is located 73 km from Uchaly. == References == Category:Rural localities in Uchalinsky District
title: Kazhayevo
